Did you know alcohol is the most used sleep aid in the world? A whopping 20–30% of insomnia patients report using alcohol as a sleep aid. While alcohol may make you sleepy, it destroys good sleep! Limit your alcohol consumption three hours before bedtime to achieve your best rest.
